'''Gabriel dos Santos Magalhães''' ({{IPA|pt|ɡabɾiˈɛw dus ˈsɐ̃tuz maɡaˈʎɐ̃js}};<ref name=":4">{{cite web |date=13 July 2023 |title=GABRIEL MAGALHÃES FORA DA COPA DO MUNDO. "SE ISSO FOI COLOCADO NA BALANÇA É UM ABSURDO!" |trans-title=GABRIEL MAGALHÃES OUT OF THE WORLD CUP. "IF THIS WAS PUT ON THE SCALE IT IS ABSURD!" |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HV-MSfXv_U8 |access-date=25 October 2023 |via=YouTube |publisher=[[De Placa]] |language=Brazilian portuguese}}</ref> born 19 December 1997), also known [[mononym]]ously as '''Gabriel''', is a Brazilian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as [[centre-back]] for {{English football updater|Arsenal}} club [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] and the [[Brazil national football team|Brazil national team]]. Known for his strength, aggression, tackling, passion and aerial threat, he is regarded as one of the best defenders in the world.<ref name="auto2">{{cite web |date=15 September 2023 |title=Ranked! The 10 best centre-backs in the world |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/best-centre-backs-defenders-in-the-world |access-date=27 October 2024 |website=FourFourTwo}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Harris |first1=Alex |last2=Potts |first2=Michael |date=24 February 2025 |title=Best defenders in the world 2025 |url=https://www.radiotimes.com/tv/sport/football/best-defenders-world/ |access-date=7 April 2025 |website=Radio Times}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=3 October 2024 |title='The pillars' – Real Madrid star admits Arsenal duo in his position have blown him away as he makes top 3 claim |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/pillars-real-madrid-star-admits-170900306.html |access-date=7 April 2025 |website=Yahoo Sports}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Collins |first1=Luke |last2=Hepburn |first2=Daniel |last3=Ritchie |first3=Calum |date=23 January 2023 |title=Ranking the 15 best centre-backs in the Premier League right now – in order |url=https://www.givemesport.com/best-centre-backs-premier-league/ |access-date=8 November 2024 |website=GiveMeSport}}</ref>

Gabriel began his senior club career at [[Avaí FC|Avaí]], having graduated from the club's youth academy in 2016. After Avaí achieved promotion to the [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] the same year, he departed for French side [[Lille OSC|Lille]]. Gabriel was loaned out to [[ES Troyes AC|Troyes]] and [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]] before returning to Lille. In 2020, he signed for [[Arsenal F.C|Arsenal]] in a deal worth £27m.<ref name="auto1">{{cite news |last=Seixas |first=Josué |date=3 December 2020 |title=The making of Gabriel: the skinny kid who went from Avaí to Arsenal |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/dec/03/the-making-of-gabriel-skinny-kid-avai-arsenal |access-date=7 April 2025 |work=The Guardian |issn=0261-3077}}</ref><ref name="auto">{{cite news |date=1 September 2020 |title=Gabriel Magalhaes: Arsenal sign Brazilian defender from Lille |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/53990363 |access-date=7 April 2025 |website=BBC Sport}}</ref> In the [[2025–26 Arsenal F.C. season|2025–26 season]], Gabriel won the [[2025–26 Premier League|Premier League]]. He also finished as a runner-up in [[2025–26 EFL Cup|EFL Cup]] and the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]], missing the decisive penalty in the latter [[2026 UEFA Champions League final|final]].

Gabriel made his international debut for Brazil in 2023.<ref>{{cite news |last=Wright |first=Stephen |date=8 April 2025 |title=Internationals: Gabriel scores first Brazil goal |url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/internationals-gabriel-scores-first-brazil-goal |access-date=7 April 2025 |publisher=Arsenal F.C.}}</ref> He scored his first international goal during [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]].<ref>{{cite web |date=9 September 2023 |title=Gabriel Magalhaes makes Brazil debut |url=https://arseblog.news/2023/09/gabriel-magalhaes-makes-brazil-debut/ |access-date=7 April 2025 |website=Arseblog News}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Avaí===
Gabriel Magalhães was born in the [[Pirituba|Pirituba District]] of [[São Paulo]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |last=Grounds |first=Nick |title=Gabriel Magalhaes: Who is Arsenal's new signing? Why is he so highly rated? |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/11964146/gabriel-magalhaes-who-is-arsenals-new-signing-why-is-he-so-highly-rated |access-date=7 April 2025 |website=Sky Sports |language=en}}</ref> At age 13, Gabriel began his career at [[Avaí FC|Avaí]] but returned to São Paulo after a week due to homesickness. However, he reconsidered his decision and returned to Avaí after two weeks, eventually going on to earn his first professional contract at age 16.<ref>{{Cite web|title=PROSPECT {{!}} Gabriel Magalhães {{!}} Get French Football News|url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2020/prospect-gabriel-magalhaes/|access-date=28 August 2020|website=www.getfootballnewsfrance.com|date=21 April 2020 }}</ref> He went on to be part of the team that won promotion to [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|Brasileiro Série A]] in 2017.<ref name=":0" />

===Lille===
[[File:Gabriel Magalhaes 2017.png|thumb|upright|Gabriel with [[ES Troyes AC|Troyes]] in 2017]]

On 31 January 2017, Gabriel joined [[Ligue 1]] side [[Lille OSC|Lille]], signing a four-and-a-half-year contract.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Gabriel Magalhaes set to join Arsenal after £27m fee agreed with Lille |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11670/12051569/gabriel-magalhaes-set-to-join-arsenal-after-gbp27m-fee-agreed-with-lille |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240621041131/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11670/12051569/gabriel-magalhaes-set-to-join-arsenal-after-gbp27m-fee-agreed-with-lille |archive-date=21 June 2024 |access-date=7 April 2025 |work=Sky Sports |language=en-GB |url-status=live }}</ref> Upon arriving in Lille, he taught himself French and went on to conduct most of his interviews in the language.<ref name=":0" /> After playing several matches for Lille II, he was loaned to fellow [[Ligue 1]] side [[ES Troyes AC|Troyes]],<ref name=":6">{{cite web|url=https://www.unibet.co.uk/blog/football/ligue-1/how-lille%E2%80%99s-gabriel-became-one-of-europe%E2%80%99s-most-coveted-young-centre-backs-1.1418748|title=How Lille's Gabriel became one of Europe's most coveted young centre-backs|publisher= Unibet|access-date=1 September 2020|language=en}}</ref> before joining Croatian side [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]], where he made just one league appearance for each club's senior team.<ref name=":7">{{cite web |title=Gabriel dos Santos Magalhães |url=https://www.losc.fr/joueur/losc-gabriel-dos-santos-magalhaes-2019-2020 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200331110120/https://www.losc.fr/joueur/losc-gabriel-dos-santos-magalhaes-2019-2020 |archive-date=31 March 2020 |access-date=3 February 2020 |publisher=Lille OSC |language=fr}}</ref>

Gabriel returned to Lille in 2018,<ref name="auto1"/> starting his first match on 10 February 2019 against relegation-threatened [[EA Guingamp|Guingamp]] in a 2–0 win. He went on to make 14 appearances over the course of the season, scoring his first goal for Lille in a 5–1 win against [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] on 14 April 2019.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title=Brazil – Gabriel – Profile with news, career statistics and history – Soccerway|url=https://us.soccerway.com/players/gabriel-dos-santos-magalhaes/433485/|access-date=28 August 2020|publisher=Soccerway}}</ref>

The following season, Gabriel began to play more regularly, forming a centre-back partnership with [[José Fonte]]. Gabriel was a starter in all six of Lille's [[2019–20 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] group stage matches.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Magee |first=Will |date=23 August 2020 |title=Meet the towering Lille defender on his way to Arsenal |url=https://inews.co.uk/sport/football/gabriel-magalhaes-lille-arsenal-transfer-news-everton-man-utd-defender-572254 |access-date=7 April 2025 |website=The i Paper |language=en-US}}</ref> On 31 January 2020, he extended his contract with Lille until 2023.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Le LOSC prolonge Gabriel jusqu'en 2023 |url=https://www.losc.fr/actualites-foot-lille/%E2%80%8Ble-losc-prolonge-gabriel-jusqu%E2%80%99en-2023 |access-date=7 April 2025 |website=losc.fr}}</ref>

Lille manager [[Christophe Galtier]] spoke about the defender's patience, saying "I saw he had great potential and he was able to seize the first opportunity he got. He was hungry to play, and while he bided his time, he worked a lot. He's an example for other youngsters to follow. It's a sort of intelligence to behave like that. How often nowadays do you see players not working if they're not in the squad?"<ref name=":2">{{Cite web |title=Gabriel: 5 things on Lille's up-and-coming Brazilian defende |url=https://www.ligue1.com/Articles/ONE%20TO%20WATCH/2020/04/16/gabriel-5-things-on-lille-defender-everton |access-date=28 August 2020 |website= |publisher=Ligue 1 |language=en}}</ref>

===Arsenal===
On 1 September 2020, Arsenal announced the signing of Gabriel Magalhães on a long-term contract.<ref>{{Cite web |date=8 April 2025 |title=Gabriel is a Gunner! {{!}} Defender joins Arsenal |url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/gabriel-gunner-defender-joins-arsenal |access-date=7 April 2025 |website=Gabriel is a Gunner! {{!}} Defender joins Arsenal |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Ames |first=Nick |date=1 September 2020 |title=Arsenal sign defender Gabriel Magalhães from Lille in £27m deal |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/sep/01/arsenal-sign-defender-gabriel-magalhaes-from-lyon-in-27m-deal |access-date=7 April 2025 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> Interest in the Brazilian was reportedly high, with multiple clubs willing to match the valuation set by Lille.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Gabriel Magalhaes set to join Arsenal after £27m fee agreed with Lille |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11670/12051569/gabriel-magalhaes-set-to-join-arsenal-after-27m-fee-agreed-with-lille |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240615151923/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11670/12051569/gabriel-magalhaes-set-to-join-arsenal-after-27m-fee-agreed-with-lille |archive-date=15 June 2024 |access-date=7 April 2025 |work=Sky Sports |language=en-GB |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Gabriel Magalhaes to Arsenal: The making of the Brazilian at Avai |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/story-telling/11095/12060865/gabriel-magalhaes-to-arsenal-the-making-of-the-brazilian-at-avai |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230516155235/https://www.skysports.com/football/story-telling/11095/12060865/gabriel-magalhaes-to-arsenal-the-making-of-the-brazilian-at-avai |archive-date=16 May 2023 |access-date=7 April 2025 |work=Sky Sports |language=en-GB |url-status=live }}</ref> Gabriel joined for a fee reaching the region of £27m after add-ons.<ref name="auto"/><ref>{{Cite web |last=Wright |first=Nick |title=Gabriel Magalhaes exclusive interview: Arsenal centre-back ready to achieve great things under Mikel Arteta |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11096/12420625/gabriel-magalhaes-exclusive-interview-arsenal-centre-back-ready-to-achieve-great-things-under-mikel-arteta |access-date=7 April 2025 |website=Sky Sports |language=en}}</ref>

====2020–21 season====
On 12 September, the opening day of the [[2020–21 Premier League|season]], Gabriel made his debut for Arsenal, scoring the second goal in a 3–0 win against [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] at [[Craven Cottage]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Begley |first=Emlyn |date=10 September 2020 |title=Fulham 0–3 Arsenal: Gabriel & Willian impress on debut in Gunners win |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/54038550 |access-date=7 April 2025 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> Following his performance in Arsenal's 2–1 win against [[West Ham United]] on 19 September 2020, Gabriel was awarded Arsenal's player of the month award for September.<ref>{{Cite web |date=8 April 2025 |title=Gabriel is our September Player of the Month! |url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/gabriel-our-september-player-month |access-date=7 April 2025 |website=Gabriel is our September Player of the Month! |language=en}}</ref> He won the award again in October after featuring in five of Arsenal's six games in the month.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Gabriel is our Player of the Month... again! |url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/gabriel-our-player-month-again |access-date=29 December 2020 |website= |publisher=Arsenal F.C. |language=en}}</ref> Arsenal manager [[Mikel Arteta]] spoke highly of Gabriel's early performances, saying "you move him from France to here at an early age, without talking the language, to adapt to a new way of playing as well... [but] he has done it really quickly and is showing a great mentality as well."<ref>{{Cite web |title='Gabriel is showing a great mentality' |url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/gabriel-showing-great-mentality |access-date=29 December 2020 |website= |publisher=Arsenal F.C. |language=en}}</ref>

Despite Arsenal's poor form in late 2020, Gabriel was awarded his third player of the month award in December after his performances in Arsenal's 1–0 win against [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] on 1 November and their 0–0 draw against [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] on 22 November.<ref>{{Cite web |date=8 April 2025 |title=🏆 Gabriel wins third Player of the Month award |url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/gabriel-wins-third-player-month-award |access-date=7 April 2025 |website=🏆 Gabriel wins third Player of the Month award |language=en}}</ref> On 29 November, Gabriel scored his first goal at the [[Emirates Stadium|Emirates]] during Arsenal's 2–1 defeat to [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Arsenal v Wolves, 2020/21 {{!}} Premier League |url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/58986 |access-date=29 December 2020 |website= |publisher=Premier League |language=en}}</ref> Gabriel received his first red card for Arsenal on 16 December in a home game against [[Southampton F.C|Southampton]], after being given two yellow cards in the space of five minutes for fouls on [[Ché Adams]] and [[Theo Walcott]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Arsenal v Southampton, 2020/21 {{!}} Premier League |url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/59016 |access-date=29 December 2020 |website= |publisher=Premier League |language=en}}</ref>

====2021–22 season====
Gabriel played in all but three of Arsenal's [[2021–22 Premier League|Premier League]] games.<ref name=":3">{{cite web |title=Games played by Gabriel in 2021/2022 |url=https://www.soccerbase.com/players/player.sd?player_id=101000&season_id=154 |access-date=12 October 2023 |website=Soccerbase}}</ref> He scored his first goal of the season in a 2–0 win against [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] at the [[King Power Stadium]] on 30 October 2021.<ref>{{Cite web |date=30 October 2021 |title=Match report: Leicester City 0–2 Arsenal |url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2021-Oct-30/leicester-city-0-2-arsenal-match-report |access-date=7 April 2025 |website=Match report: Leicester City 0–2 Arsenal |language=en}}</ref>

He scored the only goal of the game as Arsenal beat Wolverhampton Wanderers at [[Molineux Stadium|Molineux]] on 10 February,<ref>{{Cite web |last=James |first=Josh |date=10 February 2022 |title=Match report: Wolves 0–1 Arsenal |url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2022-Feb-10/wolves-0-1-arsenal-match-report |access-date=7 April 2025 |website=Match report: Wolves 0–1 Arsenal |language=en}}</ref> and also got the winning goal against West Ham in a 2–1 win at the [[London Stadium]] on 1 May.<ref>{{Cite web |date=1 May 2022 |title=Match report: West Ham 1–2 Arsenal |url=https://www.arsenal.com/premier-league-match-report-west-ham-london-stadium |access-date=7 April 2025 |website=Match report: West Ham 1–2 Arsenal |language=en}}</ref> Gabriel finished the season with five Premier League goals.<ref>{{Cite web |date=8 April 2025 |title=Gabriel |url=https://www.arsenal.com/men/players/gabrielmagalhaes |access-date=7 April 2025 |publisher=Arsenal F.C. |language=en}}</ref>

====2022–23 season====
Gabriel scored the winning goal against Fulham in the [[2022–23 Premier League|Premier League]] on 27 August 2022. He had made a mistake that allowed [[Aleksandar Mitrović]] to open the scoring, but his goal in the 86th minute gave Arsenal all three points in a 2–1 win.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Rogers |first=Jonathon |date=27 August 2022 |title=Report: Arsenal 2–1 Fulham |url=https://www.arsenal.com/premier-league-match-report-fulham-odegaard-gabriel |access-date=7 April 2025 |website=Report: Arsenal 2–1 Fulham |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Sanders |first=Emma |date=26 August 2022 |title=Arsenal 2–1 Fulham: Gabriel redeems himself with winner |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62614440 |access-date=7 April 2025 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> His partnership with [[William Saliba]] was a cornerstone of the Gunners' success throughout the season. On 21 October 2022, Arsenal announced that Gabriel had signed a new long-term contract with the club.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/gabriel-magalhaes-signs-new-long-term-contract |title=Gabriel Magalhaes signs new long-term contract |date=21 October 2022 |publisher=Arsenal F.C. |access-date=22 October 2022 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=21 October 2022 |title=Gabriel Magalhaes: Arsenal defender signs new contract until 2027 |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63350482 |access-date=7 April 2025 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> He scored the only goal of the game as Arsenal beat [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] at [[Stamford Bridge (stadium)|Stamford Bridge]] in November.<ref>{{Cite news |date=4 November 2022 |title=Chelsea 0–1 Arsenal: Gabriel scores as Gunners return to top of Premier League |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63443732 |access-date=7 April 2025 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

On 12 March 2023, he scored against Fulham again, heading in Arsenal's first goal in their 3–0 win at Craven Cottage. This was his third goal in four games against the ''Cottagers.''<ref>{{Cite web |date=12 March 2023 |title=Report: Fulham 0–3 Arsenal |url=https://www.arsenal.com/premier-league-match-report-fulham-gabriel-martinelli-odegaard-trossard |access-date=7 April 2025 |website=Report: Fulham 0–3 Arsenal |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=10 March 2023 |title=Fulham 0–3 Arsenal: Gunners restore five-point lead at top of table with convincing win |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/64852078 |access-date=7 April 2025 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

====2023–24 season====
On 17 September 2023, Gabriel made his 100th Premier League appearance in Arsenal's win against [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] at [[Goodison Park]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Rogers |first=Jonathon |date=8 April 2025 |title=Gabriel to complete Premier League century |url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/gabriel-complete-premier-league-century |access-date=7 April 2025 |website=Gabriel to complete Premier League century |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2023-Sep-17/everton-0-1-arsenal-match-report|title=Report: Everton 0–1 Arsenal|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|first=Jonathon|last=Rogers|date=17 September 2023|access-date=13 February 2024}}</ref> He scored his first goal of the [[2023–24 Arsenal F.C. season|2023–24 season]] in a 1–1 draw with [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] at [[Anfield]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=James |first=Josh |date=23 December 2023 |title=Report: Liverpool 1–1 Arsenal |url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2023-Dec-23/liverpool-1-1-arsenal-match-report |access-date=7 April 2025 |website=Report: Liverpool 1–1 Arsenal |language=en}}</ref>

Gabriel scored the first two goals in Arsenal's 5–0 win against [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] on 20 January 2024. The second goal had initially been credited as an [[own goal]] by Palace goalkeeper [[Dean Henderson]]. Arsenal appealed the decision, and the Premier League's Goal Accreditation Appeals Panel subsequently awarded the goal to Gabriel. It was his first brace for the club.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2024-Jan-20/arsenal-5-0-crystal-palace-match-report|title=Report: Arsenal 5–0 Crystal Palace|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|first=Jonathon|last=Rogers|date=20 January 2024|access-date=13 February 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/3868439|title=Arsenal defender Gabriel awarded second goal in win over Crystal Palace|publisher=Premier League|date=26 January 2024|access-date=13 February 2024}}</ref>

Gabriel made his 150th Arsenal appearance on 11 February, scoring the third goal against West Ham in a 6–0 win at the London Stadium.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2024-Feb-11/west-ham-united-0-6-arsenal-match-report|title=Report: West Ham United 0–6 Arsenal|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|first=Jonathon|last=Rogers|date=11 February 2024|access-date=13 February 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/records-we-broke-against-west-ham|title=The records we broke against West Ham|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|first=Jonathon|last=Rogers|date=12 February 2024|access-date=13 February 2024}}</ref>

==== 2024–25 season ====
On 15 September 2024, Gabriel headed in a 64th minute corner in the [[North London derby]], sealing a 1–0 away win for Arsenal.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Wright |first=Nick |title=Tottenham 0–1 Arsenal: Gabriel Magalhaes heads winner as Gunners stay on Man City's tail with derby victory |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/tottenham-vs-arsenal/report/505845 |access-date=7 April 2025 |website=Sky Sports |language=en}}</ref>

The following week, Gabriel scored the second goal of two for Arsenal during a 2–2 away draw at [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Rogers |first=Jonathon |date=22 September 2024 |title=Report: Man City 2–2 Arsenal |url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2024-Sep-22/manchester-city-2-2-arsenal-match-report |access-date=7 April 2025 |website=Report: Man City 2–2 Arsenal |language=en}}</ref> In this game he was involved in a two-team altercation after [[John Stones]] scored a 98th minute equalizer which sparked rivalry between the two teams; especially between himself and [[Erling Haaland]]. He continued this style of goalscoring, netting headers in consecutive away matches against [[Sporting C.P.]] and [[West Ham United|West Ham]] in November.<ref>{{Cite web |last=James |first=Josh |date=26 November 2024 |title=Report: Sporting CP 1–5 Arsenal |url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2024-Nov-26/sporting-cp-1-5-arsenal-match-report |access-date=7 April 2025 |website=Report: Sporting CP 1–5 Arsenal |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=James |first=Josh |date=30 November 2024 |title=Report: West Ham 2–5 Arsenal |url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2024-Nov-30/west-ham-united-2-5-arsenal-match-report |access-date=7 April 2025 |website=Report: West Ham 2–5 Arsenal |language=en}}</ref>

On 1 April 2025, Gabriel suffered a hamstring injury during a 2–1 win against Fulham, which would sideline him for the remainder of the season.<ref>{{Cite web |date=3 April 2025 |title=Gabriel To Miss The Rest Of The Season With Hamstring Injury |url=https://www.footballnewstoday.co.uk/gabriel-to-miss-the-rest-of-the-season-with-hamstring-injury |access-date=7 April 2025 |website=footballnewstoday.co.uk |language=en}}</ref> On 6 June, Gabriel signed a new long-term deal with Arsenal.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/gabriel-signs-new-arsenal-contract |title=Gabriel signs new Arsenal contract |date=6 June 2025 |publisher=Arsenal F.C. |access-date=6 June 2025 }}</ref>

==== 2025–26 season ====
During the 2025–26 season, Gabriel helped Arsenal win the [[2025–26 Premier League|Premier League title]],<ref>{{Cite web |last=Clarke |first=Adrian |url=https://www.premierleague.com/en/news/4662597/arsenal |title=Analysis: The tactics that defined Arsenal's title-winning season |access-date=2026-05-20 |website=Premier League }}</ref> scoring league goals against [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] and [[AFC Bournemouth|Bournemouth]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Wright |first=Nick |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/13488213/arsenal-4-1-aston-villa-gabriel-martin-zubimendi-leandro-trossard-and-gabriel-jesus-on-target-as-gunners-go-five-points-clear |title=Arsenal 4-1 Aston Villa: Gabriel, Martin Zubimendi, Leandro Trossard and Gabriel Jesus on target as Gunners go five points clear |publisher=Sky Sports |date=31 December 2025 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/highlights-bournemouth-2-3-arsenal |title=Highlights: Bournemouth 2-3 Arsenal |publisher=Arsenal F.C. |date=3 January 2026 }}</ref> He also scored a stoppage-time winner against [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] in a 2–1 away win.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Newcastle 1-2 Arsenal: Gabriel scores late winner as Gunners go second |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cq8edxevyw3t |access-date=2026-05-30 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

In the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]], Gabriel recorded a goal and an assist in the league phase against [[Atlético Madrid]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-05-28|title=Arsenal's route to the 2025-26 Champions League final ahead of PSG Budapest battle|url=https://www.sportsmole.co.uk/football/arsenal/champions-league/feature/arsenals-route-to-the-champions-league-final_598309.html|access-date=2026-05-30|website=Sports Mole|language=en-GB}}</ref> In the [[2026 UEFA Champions League final|final]] against [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] on 30 May 2026, he missed the decisive penalty in the shootout as Arsenal were defeated.<ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com|title=Paris vs Arsenal: UEFA Champions League 2025/26 Final|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2047742--paris-vs-arsenal/|access-date=2026-05-30|website=UEFA.com|language=en}}</ref> However, he was named in the competition's Team of the Season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/articles/brazilian-duo-uefa-names-champions-154800064.html |title=Brazilian duo in UEFA's Champions League 2025/26 best XI |publisher=Yahoo! Sports |date=31 May 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
Gabriel represented Brazil at [[Brazil national under-20 football team|under-20]] level at the [[2017 South American U-20 Championship]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Campeonato Sudamericano Sub-20 – Ecuador 2017. Lista de Jugadores |url=http://www.conmebol.com/sites/default/files/brasil_-_sudamericano_sub-20_-_ecuador_2017.pdf |access-date=23 August 2020 |website=CONMEBOL|language=es}}</ref><ref name=":0" /> On 14 November 2020, he made his international debut with [[Brazil national under-23 football team|Brazil's under-23 national team]] in a 3–1 victory against [[South Korea national under-23 football team|South Korea's under-23s]] in an international friendly.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Confira a lista dos convocados para os jogos da Seleção Olímpica contra Arábia Saudita e Egito |url=https://www.cbf.com.br/selecao-brasileira/noticias/selecao-base-masculina/confira-lista-convocacao-selecao-olimpica-jogos-arabia-saudita-e-egito |access-date=29 December 2020|publisher=Brazilian Football Confederation |language=pt}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Brazil|url=https://int.soccerway.com/teams/brazil/brazil--under-23/14044/|access-date=29 December 2020}}</ref> On 17 June 2021, he was named in the squad for the [[Football at the 2020 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2020 Summer Olympics]], but was forced to withdraw with a knee injury on 6 July.<ref>{{cite web |date=17 June 2021 |title=Seleção Olímpica é convocada para os Jogos Olímpicos de Tóquio 2020 |url=https://www.cbf.com.br/selecao-brasileira/jogos/olimpicos-de-toquio-2020/selecao-olimpica-e-convocada-para-os-jogos-olimpicos-de-toquio |access-date=17 June 2021 |publisher=Brazilian Football Confederation|language=pt}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Gabriel Magalhães sofre lesão e é cortado da seleção olímpica |url=https://ge.globo.com/rj/olimpiadas/noticia/gabriel-magalhaes-sofre-lesao-e-e-cortado-da-selecao-olimpica.ghtml |website=Globo Esporte |access-date=6 July 2021 |date=6 July 2021|language=pt}}</ref>

In August 2023, Gabriel received his first call-up to the [[Brazil national football team|Brazil senior national team]] by interim head coach [[Fernando Diniz]], for two [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches against [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]] and [[Peru national football team|Peru]].<ref>{{cite web |date=18 August 2023 |title=Fernando Diniz convoca Seleção Brasileira para a estreia das Eliminatórias |url=https://www.cbf.com.br/selecao-brasileira/noticias/selecao-masculina/fernando-diniz-convoca-a-selecao-brasileira-para-a-estreia-das-elimina |access-date=18 August 2023 |publisher=Brazilian Football Confederation |language=pt}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last1=Mota |first1=Cahê |last2=Zarko |first2=Raphael |date=18 August 2023 |title=Convocados da Seleção: veja a primeira lista de Fernando Diniz |url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/selecao-brasileira/noticia/2023/08/18/convocados-da-selecao-veja-a-primeira-lista-de-fernando-diniz.ghtml |access-date=28 August 2023 |website=[[Globo Esporte]]|language=pt}}</ref> On 9 September 2023, Gabriel debuted in a 5–1 win against [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]] during the same tournament, where he was later substituted off for [[Roger Ibañez]] in the 84th minute due to injury concerns.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/lineups/_/gameId/684578|title=Brazil 5–1 Bolivia (9 Sep, 2023) Lineups|website=ESPN |date=9 September 2023 }}</ref>

==Style of play==
Gabriel can play as part of a back three and is known for his partnership with [[William Saliba]].<ref name=":2" /> Despite his height, Gabriel is known for being fast. [[Christophe Galtier]] spoke about Gabriel, saying "He has a lot of character for a 22-year-old boy. Despite his 190cm height, he is super fast and covers his side well. He is the player who has won the most aerial duels in the first part of the season."<ref>{{Cite web|date=11 January 2020|title=Gabriel a changé de dimension et le LOSC est aux anges|url=https://www.lavoixdunord.fr/693137/article/2020-01-11/gabriel-change-de-dimension-et-le-losc-est-aux-anges|access-date=28 August 2020|website=LA VDN|language=fr}}</ref> Gabriel is also known for his distribution ability, generally looking to play the ball forward or to the left-back. In the 2019–20 season, Gabriel completed the most passes into the opposition half in all of Ligue 1.<ref>{{Cite web|date=27 August 2020|title=Gabriel Magalhães: Who is Arsenal's Latest Signing?|url=https://punditfeed.com/long-reads/gabriel-magalhaes-arsenal/|access-date=28 August 2020|website=Pundit Feed|language=en-GB}}</ref> According to his Lille teammate and mentor [[José Fonte]], Gabriel "has to keep defending well by being aggressive, being well positioned, and not taking risks."<ref name=":2" /> Furthermore, Gabriel is renowned for his aerial threat, and henceforth is known to pose a goal threat from set pieces.<ref name="auto2"/>

==Personal life==
In September 2021, Gabriel announced his engagement to his partner Gabrielle Figueiredo,<ref>{{cite news |last=Ernest |first=Victor |date=25 September 2021 |title=Gabriel Magalhaes of Arsenal proposes marriage to his girlfriend Gabrielle Figueiredo |url=https://futballnews.com/gabriel-magalhaes-proposes-marriage-to-his-girlfriend-gabrielle-figueiredo/ |access-date=12 May 2023 |website=Futball News |archive-date=21 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240221223808/https://futballnews.com/gabriel-magalhaes-proposes-marriage-to-his-girlfriend-gabrielle-figueiredo/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> and the couple got married in June 2023. Their daughter was born in March 2022, who they named Maya.<ref>{{cite news |last=Ernest |first=Victor |date=2 April 2022 |title=Gabriel Magalhães of Arsenal and his lover, Gabrielle Figueiredo welcome a baby girl named Maya |url=https://futballnews.com/gabriel-magalhaes-of-arsenal-and-his-lover-gabrielle-figueiredo-welcome-a-baby-girl-named-maya/ |access-date=12 May 2023 |website=Futball News |archive-date=18 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240518004253/https://futballnews.com/gabriel-magalhaes-of-arsenal-and-his-lover-gabrielle-figueiredo-welcome-a-baby-girl-named-maya/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> Magalhães is also cousin of the professional footballer [[Denner (footballer, born 2008)|Denner]].<ref name="Meu Timão">{{cite web |last=Fiuza |first=Matheus |date=20 December 2024 |title=Joia e titular aos 16 anos: conheça Denner, lateral-esquerdo inscrito pelo Corinthians na Copinha |url=https://www.meutimao.com.br/noticias-do-corinthians/496019/joia-e-titular-aos-16-anos-conheca-denner-lateral-esquerdo-inscrito-pelo-corinthians-na-copinha |access-date=26 February 2025 |website=Meu Timão |language=pt}}</ref>

A native of [[São Paulo]], Gabriel is a declared supporter of [[SC Corinthians Paulista|Corinthians]], despite having started his professional career at Avaí. He frequently attends matches at the [[Arena Corinthians]] during his off-season holidays in Brazil, often being spotted by fans in the stands. Gabriel has publicly expressed his desire to play for the club in the future, stating in interviews that representing Corinthians is a professional ambition and a childhood dream.<ref>{{Cite web |date=5 June 2024 |title='Por mim, amanhã estaria no Corinthians': zagueiro do Arsenal revela que 'não quer demorar' para realizar sonho |url=https://www.espn.com.br/futebol/corinthians/artigo/_/id/13749311/zagueiro-arsenal-gabriel-magalhaes-jogar-corinthians-revela-nao-quer-demorar-realizar-sonho |access-date=15 December 2025 |website=ESPN.com |language=pt}}</ref>

